There are various contraction identities of the form:
\begin{verbatim}
 g(l,t)*gam(l)*gam(m)*gam(n)*gam(r)*gam(s)*gam(t) =
     2*(gam(s)gam(m)gam(n)gam(r) + gam(r)*gam(n)*gam(m)*gam(s))
\end{verbatim}
where the sum over l and t is implied.
